Q: Alternatives to node-pty for Bun A: <p>UPDATE: bun now has native pty support. <a href="https://bun.com/blog/bun-v1.3.5#bun-terminal-api-for-pseudo-terminal-pty-support" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://bun.com/blog/bun-v1.3.5#bun-terminal-api-for-pseudo-terminal-pty-support</a></p>
<p>finally found one. ik this was posted 1 year ago, but i'm linking it in case anyone else wants it.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/bun-pty?activeTab=readme" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://www.npmjs.com/package/bun-pty</a></p>
<p><strong>usage:</strong></p>
<pre><code>import { spawn } from &quot;bun-pty&quot;;

// Create a new terminal
const terminal = spawn(&quot;bash&quot;, [], {
  name: &quot;xterm-256color&quot;,
  cols: 80,
  rows: 24
});

// Handle data from the terminal
terminal.onData((data) =&gt; {
  console.log(&quot;Received:&quot;, data);
});

// Handle terminal exit
terminal.onExit(({ exitCode, signal }) =&gt; {
  console.log(`Process exited with code ${exitCode} and signal ${signal}`);
});

// Write to the terminal
terminal.write(&quot;echo Hello from Bun PTY\n&quot;);

// Resize the terminal
terminal.resize(100, 40);

// Kill the process when done
setTimeout(() =&gt; {
  terminal.kill();
}, 5000);
</code></pre>

Q: How to make table cell horizontally scrollable and fill remaining space in FireFox browser? A: <p>In Firefox, you can't apply your overflow style directly to a <code>td</code> element, but inside it, you can apply it to a <code>div</code>:</p>
<pre class="lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>      &lt;div style=&quot;overflow-x: auto; min-width: 0;&quot;&gt;
</code></pre>
